---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Moldova Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/moldova/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Romania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/romania' },
  { title: 'Ukraine for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ukraine' },
  { title: 'Bulgaria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bulgaria' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'moldovaFit', header: 'Moldova Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MDL$8,500-12,150/mo', moldovaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MDL$9,950-14,200/mo', moldovaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MDL$7,650-10,925/mo', moldovaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MDL$7,100-10,150/mo', moldovaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Moldasig, Grawe)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'MDL$1,500-3,500/mo', moldovaFit: 'Basic' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MDL$7,650-12,150', annual: 'MDL$91,800-145,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MDL$10,500-16,200', annual: 'MDL$126,000-194,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MDL$14,100-21,750', annual: 'MDL$169,200-261,000' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MDL$300-800/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MDL$1,500-4,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Moldova 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Moldova. Europe's most affordable country, wine culture, Romanian ties, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Moldova"
  subheadline="Moldova offers Europe's most affordable living, exceptional wine culture, Romanian language ties, and warm hospitality—an emerging budget retirement destination with EU aspirations."
  heroImage="/images/countries/moldova-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Moldova</h2>
  <p>
    Moldova offers Europe's lowest cost of living, exceptional wine country (among world's largest cellars), Romanian language accessibility, and warm hospitality. For budget-conscious retirees seeking European culture at minimal cost, Moldova provides remarkable value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Chișinău is the capital with best healthcare and services. Wine regions (Cricova, Milestii Mici) offer agritourism lifestyle. Tiraspol in Transnistria offers Soviet nostalgia. Most expats choose Chișinău for healthcare access; wine country for lifestyle.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Basic; improving; Bucharest backup common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Romanian; Russian widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MDL$12,000-25,000/month (~$670-1,400 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; warm summers; cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Wine culture; hospitality; EU aspirations</li>
      <li><strong>Romania access:</strong> Same language; EU healthcare nearby</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Moldova Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Moldova healthcare is basic but improving—Medpark International Hospital in Chișinău is leading private facility. Public system underfunded. Many specialists trained in Romania or Russia. Complex cases typically go to Bucharest (4-hour drive) or EU countries.
  </p>

  <p>
    Romania provides essential backup—same language, EU healthcare standards, and easy access. International insurance with Romania/EU coverage recommended. Local care is very affordable for routine needs.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Romania Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Romania provides essential medical backup—Bucharest is 4-hour drive with excellent hospitals. Same language makes communication easy. Include Romania and EU in insurance coverage. Moldova handles routine care; Romania provides complex treatment access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Moldova has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for EU, US, and many nationalities. Very accessible for exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa Extension</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available beyond 90 days. Apply through migration office.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 90 days. Various categories including retirement. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After qualifying period. Investment options available. Moldova welcomes foreign residents.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Moldova:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance may be required</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Include Romania/EU coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Moldova</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Romania/EU coverage essential. Chișinău private hospitals handle routine care. Bucharest provides excellent backup (same language). Local insurance has age limits and limited coverage. Romania access is key component.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Moldova, EU evacuation coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Moldova</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Europe network, Romania access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Romania access:</strong> Same language, EU standards</li>
    <li><strong>Budget living:</strong> Extremely affordable daily costs</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with Romania/EU evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Moldova (MDL ~18 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Chișinău base:</strong> Best private healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Romania network:</strong> Use for complex needs</li>
    <li><strong>Budget lifestyle:</strong> Living costs extremely low</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Romanian American, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Heritage connection. Chișinău.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Romania focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MDL$8,500/month (~$470). Language ease; Bucharest backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Wine Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,600/month pension. Wine country lifestyle. Cricova region.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with EU coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MDL$11,000/month (~$610). Wine tourism; EU access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Budget Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,200/month Social Security. Maximum budget stretch. Chișinău.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with essential coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MDL$7,650/month (~$425). Budget optimization; Romania backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Moldova really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—Europe's lowest cost of living. Rent in Chișinău ~$200-400/month. Meals out ~$3-8. Quality wine $2-5/bottle. Budget $700-1,400/month covers comfortable life. Purchasing power of Western pensions goes very far.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Romanian needed?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—Romanian is official language (same as Romania). Russian also widely spoken, especially older generation. English limited outside hotels/IT sector. Learning Romanian opens Romania travel too.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Moldova safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—low crime. Avoid Transnistria region (breakaway territory). Chișinău is very safe. Normal precautions apply. Not affected by Ukraine conflict (as of now). EU candidate status brings stability focus.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the wine scene?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Exceptional—Moldova has world's largest wine cellars (Milestii Mici, Cricova). Wine is cultural centerpiece. Very affordable quality wines. Wine tourism growing. Agritourism opportunities. Perfect for wine enthusiasts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Moldova coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Moldova authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
